#: ../../source/api/quditgates.rst:2
msgid "tensorcircuit.quditgates"
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates:1
msgid "Single-qudit and two-qudit gates and their matrix representations."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates:3
msgid ""
"This module implements gates for **qudits** (d-level systems), providing "
"d-dimensional analogues of familiar qubit gates as well as qudit-specific"
" primitives."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates:6
msgid ""
"**Registry** Single-qudit builders: ``I``, ``X``, ``Z``, ``H``, ``RX``, "
"``RY``, ``RZ``, ``U8``. Two-qudit builders: ``RXX``, ``RZZ``, ``CPHASE``,"
" ``CSUM``."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates:10
msgid ""
"These names are used by higher-level APIs (e.g. "
":class:`tensorcircuit.quditcircuit.QuditCircuit`)."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.cphase_matrix_func:1
msgid "Qudit controlled-phase (``CPHASE``) gate."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.cphase_matrix_func:3
#: tensorcircuit.quditgates.csum_matrix_func:3
msgid "Logical definition:"
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.cphase_matrix_func:5
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\lvert r \\rangle \\lvert s \\rangle \\;\\longmapsto\\;\n"
"\\omega^{rs} \\lvert r \\rangle \\lvert s \\rangle"
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.cphase_matrix_func:10
#: tensorcircuit.quditgates.csum_matrix_func:10
msgid "Matrix form:"
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.cphase_matrix_func:12
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\mathrm{SUMZ}_d =\n"
"\\begin{bmatrix}\n"
"    I_d & 0   & 0   & \\cdots & 0 \\\\\n"
"    0   & Z_d & 0   & \\cdots & 0 \\\\\n"
"    0   & 0   & Z_d^2 & \\cdots & 0 \\\\\n"
"    \\vdots & \\vdots & \\vdots & \\ddots & \\vdots \\\\\n"
"    0   & 0   & 0   & \\cdots & Z_d^{d-1}\n"
"\\end{bmatrix}"
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.cphase_matrix_func:23
#: tensorcircuit.quditgates.csum_matrix_func:23
#: tensorcircuit.quditgates.swap_matrix_func:5
msgid "Qudit dimension (for each register)."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.cphase_matrix_func:25
msgid ""
"Optional control value in ``[0, d-1]``. If ``None``, builds the full SUMZ"
" block-diagonal."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.cphase_matrix_func:27
msgid "Optional primitive ``d``-th root of unity for ``Z_d``."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.cphase_matrix_func:29
msgid "``(d*d, d*d)`` matrix representing the controlled-phase."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.cphase_matrix_func:31
#: tensorcircuit.quditgates.csum_matrix_func:29
msgid "If ``cv`` is provided and is outside ``[0, d-1]``."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.csum_matrix_func:1
msgid "Qudit controlled-sum (``CSUM`` / ``SUMX``) gate."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.csum_matrix_func:5
msgid ""
"\\lvert r \\rangle \\lvert s \\rangle \\;\\longmapsto\\;\n"
"\\lvert r \\rangle \\lvert r+s \\pmod d \\rangle"
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.csum_matrix_func:12
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\mathrm{SUMX}_d =\n"
"\\begin{bmatrix}\n"
"    I_d & 0   & 0   & \\cdots & 0 \\\\\n"
"    0   & X_d & 0   & \\cdots & 0 \\\\\n"
"    0   & 0   & X_d^2 & \\cdots & 0 \\\\\n"
"    \\vdots & \\vdots & \\vdots & \\ddots & \\vdots \\\\\n"
"    0   & 0   & 0   & \\cdots & X_d^{d-1}\n"
"\\end{bmatrix}"
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.csum_matrix_func:25
msgid ""
"Optional control value in ``[0, d-1]``. If ``None``, builds the full SUMX"
" block-diagonal."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.csum_matrix_func:27
msgid "``(d*d, d*d)`` matrix representing the controlled-sum."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.h_matrix_func:1
msgid "Discrete Fourier transform (Hadamard-like) on ``d`` levels."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.h_matrix_func:3
msgid ""
"H_d\\lvert j \\rangle = \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{d}} \\sum_{k=0}^{d-1} "
"\\omega^{jk}\\lvert k \\rangle\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.h_matrix_func:5
#: tensorcircuit.quditgates.i_matrix_func:3
#: tensorcircuit.quditgates.rx_matrix_func:11
#: tensorcircuit.quditgates.ry_matrix_func:11
#: tensorcircuit.quditgates.rz_matrix_func:11
#: tensorcircuit.quditgates.s_matrix_func:5
#: tensorcircuit.quditgates.x_matrix_func:5
#: tensorcircuit.quditgates.z_matrix_func:5
msgid "Qudit dimension."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.h_matrix_func:7
#: tensorcircuit.quditgates.s_matrix_func:7
#: tensorcircuit.quditgates.z_matrix_func:7
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Optional primitive ``d``-th root of unity. Defaults to :math:`e^{2\\pi "
"i/d}`."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.h_matrix_func:9
msgid "``(d, d)`` matrix for :math:`H_d`."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.i_matrix_func:1
msgid "Identity matrix of size ``d``."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.i_matrix_func:5
msgid "``(d, d)`` identity matrix."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rx_matrix_func:1
msgid "Rotation-X (``RX``) on a selected two-level subspace of a qudit."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rx_matrix_func:3
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Acts like the qubit :math:`RX(\\theta)` on levels :math:`j` and "
":math:`k`, identity elsewhere. On the :math:`\\{\\lvert j\\rangle,\\lvert"
" k\\rangle\\}` subspace the matrix equals"
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rx_matrix_func:6
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"RX(\\theta) = \\cos\\tfrac{\\theta}{2}\\,(\\lvert j\\rangle\\!\\langle "
"j\\rvert+\\lvert k\\rangle\\!\\langle k\\rvert)\n"
"- i\\,\\sin\\tfrac{\\theta}{2}\\,(\\lvert j\\rangle\\!\\langle k\\rvert +"
" \\lvert k\\rangle\\!\\langle j\\rvert)\n"
"+ I.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rx_matrix_func:13
#: tensorcircuit.quditgates.ry_matrix_func:13
#: tensorcircuit.quditgates.rz_matrix_func:13
msgid "Rotation angle :math:`\\theta`."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rx_matrix_func:15
#: tensorcircuit.quditgates.ry_matrix_func:15
msgid "First level index."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rx_matrix_func:17
#: tensorcircuit.quditgates.ry_matrix_func:17
msgid "Second level index."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rx_matrix_func:19
msgid "``(d, d)`` matrix for :math:`RX(\\theta)` on the :math:`j,k` subspace."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rxx_matrix_func:1
msgid "Two-qudit ``RXX(\\theta)`` on a selected two-state subspace."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rxx_matrix_func:3
msgid ""
"Acts like a qubit :math:`RXX` on the subspace spanned by :math:`\\lvert "
"j1, j2\\rangle` and :math:`\\lvert k1, k2\\rangle`."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rxx_matrix_func:6
#: tensorcircuit.quditgates.rzz_matrix_func:8
msgid "Dimension of each qudit (assumed equal)."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rxx_matrix_func:10
#: tensorcircuit.quditgates.rxx_matrix_func:12
msgid "Level on qudit-1."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rxx_matrix_func:14
#: tensorcircuit.quditgates.rxx_matrix_func:16
msgid "Level on qudit-2."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rxx_matrix_func:18
msgid ""
"``(d*d, d*d)`` matrix representing :math:`RXX(\\theta)` on the selected "
"subspace."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.ry_matrix_func:1
msgid "Rotation-Y (``RY``) on a selected two-level subspace of a qudit."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.ry_matrix_func:3
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Acts like the qubit :math:`RY(\\theta)` on levels :math:`j` and "
":math:`k`, identity elsewhere. On the :math:`\\{\\lvert j\\rangle,\\lvert"
" k\\rangle\\}` subspace the matrix equals"
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.ry_matrix_func:6
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"RY(\\theta) = \\cos\\tfrac{\\theta}{2}\\,(\\lvert j\\rangle\\!\\langle "
"j\\rvert+\\lvert k\\rangle\\!\\langle k\\rvert)\n"
"+ \\sin\\tfrac{\\theta}{2}\\,(\\lvert k\\rangle\\!\\langle j\\rvert - "
"\\lvert j\\rangle\\!\\langle k\\rvert)\n"
"+ I.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.ry_matrix_func:19
msgid "``(d, d)`` matrix for :math:`RY(\\theta)` on the :math:`j,k` subspace."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rz_matrix_func:1
msgid "Rotation-Z (``RZ``) on a selected level of a qudit."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rz_matrix_func:3
msgid ""
"Acts like the qubit :math:`RZ(\\theta)` but applies a phase only to level"
" :math:`j`. On the computational basis it equals"
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rz_matrix_func:6
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"RZ(\\theta) = I + (e^{i\\theta}-1)\\,\\lvert j\\rangle\\!\\langle "
"j\\rvert,\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rz_matrix_func:9
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"i.e. :math:`\\lvert j\\rangle \\mapsto e^{i\\theta}\\,\\lvert j\\rangle` "
"and all other levels unchanged."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rz_matrix_func:15
msgid "Level index receiving the phase."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rz_matrix_func:17
msgid ""
"``(d, d)`` diagonal matrix implementing :math:`RZ(\\theta)` on level "
":math:`j`."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rzz_matrix_func:1
msgid "Two-qudit ``RZZ(\\theta)`` on a selected two-state subspace."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rzz_matrix_func:3
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Acts like a qubit "
":math:`RZZ(\\theta)=\\exp(-i\\,\\tfrac{\\theta}{2}\\,\\sigma_z)` on the "
"two-dimensional subspace spanned by :math:`\\lvert j1, j2\\rangle` and "
":math:`\\lvert k1, k2\\rangle`, and as identity elsewhere. The resulting "
"block is diagonal with phases :math:`\\mathrm{diag}(e^{-i\\theta/2},\\, "
"e^{+i\\theta/2})`."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rzz_matrix_func:12
msgid "Level on qudit-1 for the first basis state."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rzz_matrix_func:14
msgid "Level on qudit-1 for the second basis state."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rzz_matrix_func:16
msgid "Level on qudit-2 for the first basis state."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rzz_matrix_func:18
msgid "Level on qudit-2 for the second basis state."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rzz_matrix_func:20
msgid "``(d*d, d*d)`` matrix representing subspace :math:`RZZ(\\theta)`."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.rzz_matrix_func:22
msgid "If indices are out of range or select the same basis state."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.s_matrix_func:1
msgid "Diagonal phase gate ``S_d`` on ``d`` levels."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.s_matrix_func:3
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"S_d\\lvert j \\rangle = \\omega^{j(j+p_d)/2}\\lvert j \\rangle,\\quad p_d"
" = (d \\bmod 2)\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.s_matrix_func:9
msgid "``(d, d)`` diagonal matrix for :math:`S_d`."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.swap_matrix_func:1
msgid "SWAP gate for two qudits of equal dimension :math:`d`."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.swap_matrix_func:3
msgid ""
"Exchanges basis states :math:`\\lvert i\\rangle\\lvert j\\rangle \\to "
"\\lvert j\\rangle\\lvert i\\rangle`."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.swap_matrix_func:7
msgid "``(d^2, d^2)`` permutation matrix implementing SWAP."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.u8_matrix_func:1
msgid "``U8`` diagonal single-qudit gate for prime dimensions."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.u8_matrix_func:3
msgid ""
"See ref: Howard, Mark, and Jiri Vala. \"Qudit versions of the qubit "
"\\pi/8 gate.\" Physical Review A 86, no. 2 (2012): 022316. "
"https://doi.org/10.1103/PhysRevA.86.022316"
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.u8_matrix_func:7
msgid ""
"This gate is the qudit analogue of the qubit :math:`\\pi/8` gate, defined"
" in *Howard & Campbell, Phys. Rev. A 86, 022316 (2012)*. It is diagonal "
"in the computational basis with exponents determined by modular "
"polynomials in the parameters :math:`\\gamma, z, \\epsilon`. These gates,"
" together with Pauli and Clifford operations, generate the full single-"
"qudit Clifford hierarchy."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.u8_matrix_func:13
msgid ""
"For :math:`d=2`, this reduces (up to global phase) to the standard qubit "
":math:`\\pi/8` gate."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.u8_matrix_func:15
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"For :math:`d=3`, the exponents live in :math:`\\mathbb{Z}_9` and the "
"primitive ninth root :math:`\\zeta = e^{2\\pi i/9}` is used."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.u8_matrix_func:17
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"For prime :math:`d>3`, the construction uses the modular inverse of 12 in"
" :math:`\\mathbb{Z}_d`."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.u8_matrix_func:20
msgid "Qudit dimension (must be prime)."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.u8_matrix_func:22
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Shear parameter :math:`\\gamma' \\in \\mathbb{Z}_d`. If :math:`gamma = "
"0`, the gate is a diagonal Clifford. If :math:`gamma \\neq 0`, the gate "
"is a genuine non-Clifford (analogue of :math:`\\pi/8`)."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.u8_matrix_func:26
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Displacement parameter :math:`z' \\in \\mathbb{Z}_d`, which sets the "
"symplectic part of the associated Clifford."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.u8_matrix_func:29
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Phase offset parameter :math:`\\epsilon' \\in \\mathbb{Z}_d`. It only "
"contributes a global phase factor :math:`\\omega^{\\epsilon'}`."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.u8_matrix_func:32
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Optional primitive :math:`d`-th root of unity (complex). Defaults to "
":math:`e^{2\\pi i/d}` for d>3, and :math:`e^{2\\pi i/9}` for d=3."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.u8_matrix_func:35
msgid "``(d, d)`` diagonal matrix of dtype ``npdtype``."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.u8_matrix_func:37
msgid ""
"If ``d`` is not prime; if 12 has no modular inverse mod ``d`` (for "
"``d>3``); or if the computed exponents do not sum to 0 mod ``d`` (or 0 "
"mod 3 for ``d=3``)."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.x_matrix_func:1
msgid "Generalized Pauli-X on a ``d``-level system."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.x_matrix_func:3
msgid ""
"X_d\\lvert j \\rangle = \\lvert (j+1) \\bmod d \\rangle\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.x_matrix_func:7
msgid "``(d, d)`` matrix for :math:`X_d`."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.z_matrix_func:1
msgid "Generalized Pauli-Z on a ``d``-level system."
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.z_matrix_func:3
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Z_d\\lvert j \\rangle = \\omega^{j}\\lvert j \\rangle,\\quad "
"\\omega=e^{2\\pi i/d}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: of tensorcircuit.quditgates.z_matrix_func:9
msgid "``(d, d)`` matrix for :math:`Z_d`."
msgstr ""

